      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does the Kérastase Genesis serum do?",
            "content": "<p>It’s a daily leave-in scalp serum for weakened hair that’s prone to falling from breakage. Powered by Aminexil, Edelweiss Native Cells, and Ginger Root, it strengthens hair, helps re-anchor the follicle, and reduces hair-fall.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does it treat hair fall at the root or from breakage?",
            "content": "<p>Both — and Genesis splits the work across the range: the Serum targets hair-fall at the root, while the shampoo and conditioner help guard against fibre breakage. Tackling both causes together is what sets the range apart.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How and when do I apply it?",
            "content": "<p>Apply the jelly-textured serum directly to a clean scalp daily and massage in. It’s a leave-in (no rinsing), and the gel-like texture stays put without dripping.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will it regrow hair on bald spots?",
            "content": "<p>No. It’s a fortifying, anti-hair-fall serum that strengthens and protects the hair you have and supports a healthier scalp environment — it isn’t a regrowth treatment for areas where hair is already gone.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
